        <para>The publications you catalogue must be uniquely identifiable.
            This allows the database to access information about the publication from other sources. There are several of these unique
            identifiers such as the ISBN number, which is assigned to recently published books and edited volumes; recently published periodicals and
            series have a corresponding ISSN number. Individual publications (and parts of publications) on all levels may have a DOI, a
            Digital Object Identifier, which is a digital identifier for objects both print and digital. </para>
        <para>If any of these numbers are available to you when cataloguing the publication, make sure to assign the appropriate identifier.</para>
